<title type="html"><![CDATA[Moving a sprite!]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6215&amp;p=58978#p58978"><![CDATA[
You guessed correctly that it has something to do with two's complement. When you subtract <em>n</em> on a 6502, you actually add 255-<em>n</em>. To make the subtraction work as expected, you need to set the carry so that you add 255-<em>n</em>+1 = 256-<em>n</em> = -<em>n</em> (mod 256).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Wed Mar 24, 2010 3:29 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
